Hi just trying to get my head around XAML.
Thought that I would try some writing XAML in code.
Trying to add a grid with 6 by 6 column definitions then add a textblock into one of the grid cells.
I dont seem to be able to reference the cell that I want - there is no method on the grid that I can add the textblock too.  Just grid.children.add(object).  No Cell definition.
TIA
The XAML
<Page x:Class="WPF_Tester.Page1"     xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"     xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"     Title="Page1"     Loaded="Page_Loaded"> </Page>
The C# private void Page_Loaded(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)         {
//create the structure          Grid g = new Grid();         g.ShowGridLines = true;         g.Visibility = Visibility.Visible;           //add columns         for (int i = 0; i < 6; ++i)         {             ColumnDefinition cd = new ColumnDefinition();             cd.Name = "Column" + i.ToString();              g.ColumnDefinitions.Add(cd);         }         //add rows         for (int i = 0; i < 6; ++i)         {             RowDefinition rd = new RowDefinition();             rd.Name = "Row" + i.ToString();              g.RowDefinitions.Add(rd);         }         TextBlock tb = new TextBlock();         tb.Text = "Hello World";          g.Children.Add(tb);      }
